This paper is primarily focused on the generalization properties of machine learning algorithms, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of information-theoretic measures such as Conditional Mutual Information (CMI) is also a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses methods for adaptive data analysis, which is a topic that is often studied in the sub-field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also touches on the topic of differential privacy, which is a sub-field of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of compression schemes, which is a topic that is often studied in the sub-field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
